{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> οἶκτος</b>, ὁ, <br /> (οἴζω) <b>pity, compassion,</b> οἶ. δ᾽ ἕλε λαὸν ἅπαντα [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 2.81, compare 24.438 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; οἶ. τις ἴσχει ἀποκτεῖναι <b>a feeling of pity</b> prevents him from.., [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 5.92.γ,compare 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 3.40; οἴκτου πλέως 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Philoctetes” 1074; ἔχειν οἶκτον φρενί [prev. author] “Aj.” 525; ἐμοὶ γὰρ οἶ. δεινὸς εἰσέβη [prev. author] “Tr.” 298; ἐμοὶ μὲν οἶ. δεινὸς ἐμπέπτωκέ τις [prev. author] “Ph.” 965; θνητοὺς.. ἐν οἴκτῳ προθέμενος 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Prometheus Vinctus” 241; δι᾽ οἴκτου ἔχειν τινά 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Hecuba” 851; εἰσῆλθέ μ᾽ οἶ. εἰ.. [prev. author] “Med.” 931 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: with <i>genitive</i> objecti, <b>compassion for..,</b> πόθος καὶ οἶ. τῆς πόλιος [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 1.165, compare 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Hecuba” 519: in 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Supplices” 486, οἰκτίσας ἰδών (2nd-3rd c.AD: Hermes Trismegistus) should be read for οἶκτος εἰσιδών. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> <b>lamentation, piteous wailing,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Simonides Lyricus 4.3; οἶ. οὔτις ἦν διὰ στόμα 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Septem contra Thebas” 51; τόνδε κλύουσαν οἶ. [prev. author] “Ch.” 411 (Lyric poetry); οἶκτον [οἰκτρὸν] ἀΐων [prev. author] “Supp.” 59 (Lyric poetry); κλύω τινὸς οἴκτου 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Trachiniae” 864; οὐκ οἴκτου μέτα [prev. author] “OC” 1636: _plural_, παθόντος οἴκτοις\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] <b>by the wailings</b> of the sufferer, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Supplices” 386 (Lyric poetry); ἄϊον οἴκτους οὓς οἰκτίζῃ 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Troades” 155 (_anapaest meter_); τοὺς ὀδ